AB  - Accessible summary This study is about transition from school to work in Austria. In Austria, students with intellectual disabilities leave school earlier than other students. Many students with intellectual disabilities join sheltered workshops. This means that students with intellectual disabilities in Austria do not have the same choices as other people. This leads to disadvantages in the lives of the students with intellectual disabilities. Learning helps people to take decisions independently. The right to learn is very important, also for people with disabilities.
